Idea

Add the two binary strings from right to left (like manual addition).

Keep a carry:

Add digits from both strings + carry
Compute:
sum % 2 → current bit
sum / 2 → new carry

Finally, reverse the result.



C++--------------

class Solution {
public:
    string addBinary(string a, string b) {
        int i = a.size() - 1;
        int j = b.size() - 1;
        int carry = 0;
        string res = "";
        
        while(i >= 0 || j >= 0 || carry){
            int sum = carry;
            
            if(i >= 0) sum += a[i--] - '0';
            if(j >= 0) sum += b[j--] - '0';
            
            res += (sum % 2) + '0';
            carry = sum / 2;
        }
        
        reverse(res.begin(), res.end());
        return res;
    }
};


------------------------

Example

Input
a = "1010"
b = "1011"

Step-by-step:

   1010
 + 1011
-------
  10101

Output:

"10101"
Key Insight

Binary addition is just like decimal addition, but:

Base is 2 instead of 10
So carry happens when sum ≥ 2
